{
  "texts": [
    "The peak at 1005 cm -1 appears in both the Raman (glass) and SERS (AgF@AgM@C10) spectra.",
    "We fabricated a mesoporous Ag film on SiO 2 and coated it with decylphenyl groups (AgM@C10, Suppl.",
    "When using glass as the baseline, flat AgM@C10 generated 5× more SERS signal than glass.",
    "AgF@AgM@C10 shows the highest EF of 10× because the volume of the EM-field in pores is large and generates bigger Raman absorbance than the flat AgM@C10 surface (Fig. 3h).",
    "These findings confirm the critical role of macropores in enhancing Raman scattering of MPs."
  ]
}